00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:14,730
Oh, right, the schedule ...

209
00:15:15,430 --> 00:15:19,390
Tomorrow there's a memorial service for the death anniversary of Chairman Han's oldest son,

210
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:21,360
and also a shareholders' meeting.

211
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:24,250
The meeting must be happening because of the shares I handed over.

212
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:27,120
Let's just be there so we're not late for the meeting.

213
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:31,320
By the way, if you stay out again, will they let it slide?

214
00:15:36,230 --> 00:15:40,660
I let it slip once and now she stays out like it's second nature.

215
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:42,130
Are you sure she's at work?

216
00:15:42,130 --> 00:15:46,560
Wherever she is, I hope she's there at the memorial service.

217
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:52,370
There are not many people attending, so having the Chairwoman of Yumin Foundation would look good for us.

218
00:15:52,370 --> 00:15:55,190
Is looking good so important to you?

219
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:58,860
Why did you even come up with the memorial service?

220
00:15:58,860 --> 00:16:03,560
I'm so frustrated holding the service with just a few family members.

221
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:07,170
How could you say that?

222
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:15,120
It's better if I believed he lives somewhere far away,

223
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:20,450
but holding this memorial service as if it's a special day reminds me that my son is dead.

224
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:24,310
Mother-in-law ...

225
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:29,480
You love your oldest son so much ...

226
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:36,820
What a waste, if he were alive, both your love and your stock would be all his.

227
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:39,090
Hey! By the way,

228
00:16:39,090 --> 00:16:42,470
is Seong Wun not home either?

229
00:16:42,470 --> 00:16:46,630
These two ... Are they acting up as a couple or what?

230
00:16:59,740 --> 00:17:04,060
I knew you'd come.

231
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:05,880
How dare you call me?

232
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:09,160
You came anyway, even though you didn't have to.

233
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:12,880
I knew I could rely on you.

234
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:16,350
- Were you destroyed by your older sister? 
 - What?

235
00:17:16,350 --> 00:17:20,930
What? "Destroyed" is not slang, it's standard language.

236
00:17:20,930 --> 00:17:26,110
By the way, don't you think at all when doing something?

237
00:17:26,110 --> 00:17:28,710
I mean ... Do you even have a brain?

238
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:31,760
Why call me when all this is happening?

239
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:38,530
Because of your perfect diction, it definitely hits differently when you swear at me.

240
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:43,660
Before I start swearing at you with perfect diction, don't ever call me again.

241
00:17:43,660 --> 00:17:46,070
Do you think I'm here because I still have feelings for you?

242
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:47,810
I came to warn you.

243
00:17:47,810 --> 00:17:52,030
You better stop acting up because your life hurts and be quiet.

244
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:55,500
My life is still not hurting.

245
00:17:57,370 --> 00:18:00,410
Yours is not hurting?

246
00:18:00,410 --> 00:18:02,260
What are you talking about?

247
00:18:02,260 --> 00:18:04,990
Why would I tell you that?

248
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:07,790
Enjoy drinking for the last time and go home.

249
00:18:07,790 --> 00:18:13,960
Tomorrow, after the shareholders' meeting, you will be ignored.

250
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:30,000
What's up?

251
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:34,470
Now you're Chief District Prosecutor, are you saying you're above the Chief of Seopyeong Branch?

252
00:18:34,470 --> 00:18:35,960
You haven't contacted me once.

253
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:38,090
I have no time to joke around. What is it?

254
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:41,000
Why are you acting all busy?

255
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,720
You know the Hanju's daughter-in-law case that got you transferred here in the past?

256
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:44,980
 Yes, what about it? 

257
00:18:44,980 --> 00:18:47,850
You know the kid who took charge of it? Ahn Yu Jun?

258
00:18:47,850 --> 00:18:51,230
 I was looking for him because I had some work for him. 

259
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,010
